Mine Rescue operations have declared it unsafe to go any further due to rockfalls that occurred earlier on Wednesday.Masina said he was concerned about every day that passes with no sign of the boy."We are dreading the eventuality of the likely outcome " said Masina.The mayor said the Disaster and Emergency Management services and the Mine Rescue Services had done everything they could in the rescue operations but could not go any further.CEO of Mine Rescue Services Christo de Klerk said: "It will not be possible to continue without endangering the life of any person."- TMG Digital/TimesLIVE